                <h1>Who Were the 12 Disciples of Jesus?</h1>
                <p>The 12 disciples, also known as the apostles, were chosen by Jesus to spread his teachings. They include Peter, James, John, Andrew, Philip, Bartholomew, Matthew, Thomas, James the Less, Thaddeus, Simon the Zealot, and Judas Iscariot, who betrayed Him. Each disciple played a vital role in the early Christian church.</p>
